    <stitle>PROPELLER SHAFT - ASSEMBLE - SNAP RING YOKE UNIVERSAL JOINT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="5">
        <title>SNAP RING YOKE UNIVERSAL JOINT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pack the cross journal cavities with grease before assembly using a grease gun at the
                lubrication fitting (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0600118">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0600118" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0600118" filename="../figg06/G0600118.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Pack Cross Journal Cavities With Grease Before Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pack the bearing cap about &#188; full with grease.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position cross in the propeller shaft yoke with its lube fitting on the inboard side
                (towards propeller shaft) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0600119">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0600119" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0600119" filename="../figg06/G0600119.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Position Cross in Propeller Shaft Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move one end of the cross so that a journal protrudes out of a cross hole in the yoke.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a bearing cap onto the journal and align it to the cross hole (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0600120">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0600120" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0600120" filename="../figg06/G0600120.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Place Bearing Cap onto Journal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press the bearing cap into the yoke just enough to install a snap ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a snap ring.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When installing the snap ring, be sure that it is seated in the groove.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the other end of the cross so its journal protrudes out of the opposite cross hole in
                the yoke.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a bearing cap onto the journal and align it to the cross hole (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0600121">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0600121" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0600121" filename="../figg06/G0600121.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Place Bearing Cap onto Journal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press the bearing cap into the yoke just enough to install the other snap ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a snap ring.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the joint is stiff, strike the yoke with a soft hammer to free up binding. (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0600122">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0600122" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0600122" filename="../figg06/G0600122.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Strike Yoke to Free Up Binding</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
